## Notes on controller behavior to understand
- `POST /integrations/jira/connect` calls `initiateConnect({ companyId, userId })` from `req.user`, returns `{ url }` 
- `GET /integrations/jira/callback` catches errors and redirects with `?error=jira_connect_failed` on failure, redirects with `?connected=jira` on success. The redirect URL base comes from `EnvConfigService.get({ key: FRONTEND_URL })`.
- `DELETE /integrations/jira/installations/:id` calls `disconnect({ installationDbId, companyId })` and returns 204

Read the controller at `/Users/4thwithme/Documents/repo/no-name-proj/backend/src/modules/jira/jira.controller.ts` if you need to understand exact behavior before writing tests.

